==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[masticatus]], past participle of [[masticare]] to [[chew]], probably from [[mastiche]] [[mastic]]. See Mastic.

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-masticate.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
'''masticate'''
#To [[chew]] [[food]].
#:''The cow stood, quietly '''masticating''' its [[cud]].''
#To [[grind]] or [[knead]] something into a [[pulp]].

